## Common Pitfalls to Avoid

### 1. Premature Completion
- Declaring done without checking all files
- Assuming structure means content is complete
- Not testing navigation and links
- Skipping reference validation

### 2. Incomplete Verification
- Only checking file existence, not content
- Not following links to verify they work
- Missing cross-reference validation
- Ignoring empty directories

### 3. Quality Issues
- Accepting placeholder content
- Not verifying technical accuracy
- Inconsistent formatting/style
- Missing error scenarios

## Enforcement

### When to Apply These Rules
1. Before declaring any task complete
2. After generating documentation sets
3. Before committing/pushing changes
4. During code review preparation
5. At project milestones

### Consequences of Skipping Verification
- Incomplete deliverables
- Broken user experience
- Technical debt accumulation
- Rework required later
- Loss of credibility

